data.oai_dc:dc: Material examined from the Nunn Member of the Lake Valley Formation in New Mexico. UMMP numbers are those illustrated and types for new species which are housed at the University of Michigan Museum of Paleontology. M localities are those collected by Brad Macurda and students while he was at the University of Michigan. KNM specimens were donated by Barry Kues of the University of New Mexico. LNM specimens come from the Lowell Laudon collection, also donated by Barry Kues. IU specimens were collected by A. S. Horowitz and J. H. Johnson of Indiana University, which came with Macurda's collection. FC specimens were those collected by the authors. All these specimens are housed with the University of Michigan. All other specimens are part of the Springer Collection of the U.S. National Museum of Natural History (USNM).
